89	14	json	[{"model": "technicalguides.guide", "pk": 14, "fields": {"title": "Internal micro SD card replacement", "device": 20, "text": "<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Download and install&nbsp;<a href=\\"https://etcher.io/\\">Etcher</a> program.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Download <a href=\\"ftp://pb_service:86pBQUWvAt@31.42.51.146/sdcard/840/840_detectsn.zip\\">service image for SDSN</a> (SD card serial number) detection.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Burn the image to the known good micro SD card with Etcher program.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Insert microSD card with the burned image into the device card reader and turn on the device by pressing &lsquo;power on button&rsquo; for 1 sec.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>SDSN should appear on the display (device should turn off by itself in a few seconds; SDSN should be on the display).</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open Jenkins builder using direct link <a href=\\"https://tickets.obreey-products.com/jenkins/\\">Jenkins</a> and log in.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Select &lsquo;840-sdcard&rsquo; in the appeared list of projects.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Find a label with waveform (WF) and VCOM values.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li style=\\"text-align: center;\\"><img alt=\\"\\" src=\\"/media/uploads/2017/12/07/840vcom-wf.png\\" style=\\"height:150px; width:262px\\" /></li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Put SDSN and device serial number, WF and VCOM into the empty fields of Jenkins builder, select your e-mail from the drop-down list and press &rsquo;Build&rsquo; button.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Open selected in previous point e-mail box and download image archive, using link from the received message. Please double check the &lsquo;spam&rsquo; or &lsquo;junk&rsquo; folders if no e-mail received.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Unzip the archive and burn the appeared firmware image to the known good micro SD card with Etcher&nbsp; program.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Insert micro SD card with the burned image into the device card reader.&nbsp;</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Turn on the device with a &#39;power&#39; button - power led should light in green and &lsquo;welcome screen&rsquo; of a service mode should appear. 1If power led doesn&rsquo;t light in green and there is no &lsquo;welcome screen&rsquo; - please hold power button for 15 sec and then connect device to the USB charger.&nbsp;</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Following the instructions on display, make primary device settings.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Power on the device and connect it via USB cable to your PC.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Provide additional diagnostic procedures if needed (touch screen, Wi-Fi, etc.)</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Copy &lsquo;Content&rsquo; folders to the root catalog of the internal microSD card of the device. Content is the same for all devices of this model and can be used constantly once downloaded. Link for downloading can be found in the e-mail message with firmware image archive download link. Please be noted, that mass-production content may differ from a customized (B2B) projects content.</li>\\r\\n</ol>", "published_date": "2017-12-07T13:26:40.831Z", "updated_date": "2017-12-07T13:26:40.831Z", "group": [3]}}]	Internal micro SD card replacement	8	89	default
