207	66	json	[{"model": "technicalguides.guide", "pk": 66, "fields": {"title": "Primary diagnostic procedure", "device": 3, "text": "<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Read and understand customers claim. Clarify if needed.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Provide visual inspection of the device. Pay special attention to:</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul style=\\"margin-left:40px\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>case (covers) their corners and joints.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>ports (USB, jack, micro SD card reader slot, etc).</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>display (please refer to the &ldquo;display mechanical damages clarification file&rdquo; in order to provide better diagnostic).</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Clarify device serial number and needed FW version.</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>If device doesn&rsquo;t power on (or doesn&rsquo;t load into the main menu):</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Remove the back cover and measure the battery voltage - battery charge level value should be more or equal to 3.9V&nbsp;(charge or replace battery if needed). Please provide charging for at lest 8h and with known operational external charger and USB cable.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Try to power on.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>If no result, please replace internal memory microSD card with bootable known good microSD card for this particular model (or create it using <a href=\\"http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/515%20%7C%20Mini/Internal%20micro%20SD%20card%20replacement\\">instruction</a>). Or insert into the card reader of the device a microSD card with SDSN (SD card serial number) detection burned on it.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Try to power on.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>If no result, please use <a href=\\"http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/515%20%7C%20Mini/Internal%20micro%20SD%20card%20replacement\\">Unit Replacement Program procedure</a>.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>After receiving the replacement unit reset the serial number and update FW to the needed version.</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>If device powers on:</strong></p>\\r\\n\\r\\n