85	Software Recovery for device with NAND	<hr />\r\n<p style="margin-left:80px"><strong>For device with&nbsp;V2.1 PCB</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:120px"><a href="/media/uploads/2018/04/24/img_20180424_151023-1.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="/media/uploads/2018/04/24/img_20180424_151023-1.jpg" style="height:239px; width:340px" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Download,&nbsp;unzip&nbsp;and instal&nbsp;<a href="ftp://pb_service:86pBQUWvAt@31.42.51.146/PhoenixSuit_V1.10.rar" target="_blank">PhoenixSuit</a></li>\r\n\t<li>Download, unzip&nbsp;and install&nbsp;<a href="ftp://pb_service:86pBQUWvAt@31.42.51.146/626/PB626_SDSN_NAND.zip">service image for SDSN</a></li>\r\n\t<li>Run &#39;PhoenixSuit&#39;, go to &#39;Firmware&#39; tab&nbsp;and&nbsp;select&nbsp;&#39;<em><strong>PB626_SDSN_NAND.img&#39;&nbsp;</strong></em>file</li>\r\n\t<li>Press and hold&nbsp;&#39;Menu&#39; button, while conecting USB cable to turned off device.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:120px"><img alt="" src="/media/uploads/2018/04/24/photo_2018-04-24_14-28-35.jpg" style="height:118px; width:320px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start="5">\r\n\t<li>Press &quot;YES&quot; in each of two dialog boxes of &#39;PhoenixSuit&#39; when they appear.</li>\r\n\t<li>When firmware process is finished,&nbsp;SDSN&nbsp;of the device will&nbsp;appear in&nbsp;display.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:120px"><img alt="" src="/media/uploads/2018/04/24/photo_2018-04-24_14-28-29.jpg" style="height:156px; width:320px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start="7">\r\n\t<li>Go to Jenkins builder using direct link&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://tickets.obreey-products.com/jenkins/">Jenkins&nbsp;</a>and log in.&nbsp;Select &lsquo;626-serviced&rsquo; in the appeared list of projects.&nbsp;</li>\r\n\t<li>Select display type, for XH7 put WF and VCOM level to the empty fields of Jenkins builder.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>VCOM must be specified in millivolts. Example:<br />\r\nValue on the panels FPC: -3.07<br />\r\nValue in Jenkins form: -3070</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="/media/uploads/2017/12/06/xh7wf.png" style="height:150px; width:274px" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="/media/uploads/2017/12/06/xh7vcom.png" style="height:150px; width:158px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start="10">\r\n\t<li>Open your e-mail box (selected in previous point)&nbsp;and download image archive, using link from the received message. Please double check the &lsquo;spam&rsquo; or &lsquo;junk&rsquo; folders if no e-mail received.</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Unzip the archive and copy the appeared SWUPDATE.BIN file to the root catalog of internal memory of the device.</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p>Press &#39;Forward&#39; button on the turned on device for start&nbsp;firmware proces</p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:120px">&nbsp;<img alt="" src="/media/uploads/2018/04/24/photo_2018-04-24_14-27-56_LcphnGf.jpg" style="height:113px; width:320px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start="13">\r\n\t<li>Following the instructions on display, make primary device settings.</li>\r\n\t<li>Provide additional diagnostic procedures if needed (touch screen, Wi-Fi, etc.)</li>\r\n\t<li>Copy &lsquo;Content&rsquo; folders to the root catalog of the internal microSD card of the device. Content is the same for all devices of this model and can be used constantly once downloaded. Link for downloading can be found in the e-mail message with firmware image archive download link. Please be noted, that mass-production content may differ from a customized (B2B) projects content.</li>\r\n\t<li>Reset device to factory defaults using internal Settings menu of the device.</li>\r\n</ol>	2018-06-06 12:32:34.268118+00	2018-06-06 12:32:34.268182+00	11
9	Unit Replacement Procedure	<ol start="1">\r\n\t<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;After receiving of new unit unpack it and provide visual inspection. Pay special attention to:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>-&nbsp;case (covers) their corners and joints.</li>\r\n\t<li>- ports (USB, jack, micro SD card reader slot, etc).</li>\r\n\t<li>- display (please refer to the &ldquo;display mechanical damages clarification file&rdquo; in order to provide better diagnostic procedures).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n\t<li>Do not use retail box, cables or documents from the received unit.</li>\r\n\t<li>Put the defective device into the received retail box instead of received one.</li>\r\n\t<li>Return the defective device once it is requested.</li>\r\n\t<li>Remove the back cover of the received device and make&nbsp;<a href="http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/626+%20%7C%20Touch%20Lux%203/Internal%20micro%20SD%20card%20replacement">internal micro SD card replacement procedure</a>&nbsp;<strong><em><u>using the serial number of the defective device</u></em></strong><em>.</em></li>\r\n\t<li>Remove serial number sticker from back cover of old device and stick to the swap unit</li>\r\n\t<li>Provide additional visual inspection of the display (pay special attention to the lines, dots, spots and front light quality).</li>\r\n\t<li>Check touch screen reaction (run &lsquo;Scribble&rsquo; application and try to draw a grid).</li>\r\n\t<li>Check Wi-Fi connection.</li>\r\n\t<li>Check micro SD card slot.</li>\r\n\t<li>Check PC connection.</li>\r\n</ol>	2017-12-06 15:16:41.040985+00	2017-12-07 10:10:39.378179+00	11
