58	Power consumption	<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">In order to provide proper consumption measurements, please follow next steps:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">1. Battery charge level value should be more or equal to 3.9 V.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">2. Last version of FW is&nbsp;mandatory. Please update if needed.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">3. Connect the ampere-meter to the battery contacts.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">4. Measure consumption values for different modes and compare with the table:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellspacing="0">\r\n\t<tbody>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;Stand-by</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;5 mА</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;Locked</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;5 mА</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;Power off&nbsp;</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;40 uА&nbsp;</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>20% values dispersion is&nbsp;acceptable.</p>	2017-12-11 14:39:29.164262+00	2017-12-12 14:19:09.726682+00	3
