66	Primary diagnostic procedure	<p>For such procedure you will need:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Plastic or metal blade.</li>\r\n\t<li>SDSN (SD card serial number) detection microSD card.</li>\r\n\t<li>External PC card reader.</li>\r\n\t<li>Known operational external charger and USB cable.</li>\r\n\t<li>Volt-ampere-meter</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Read and understand customers claim. Clarify, if needed.</li>\r\n\t<li>Clarify device serial number and actual FW version.</li>\r\n\t<li>Provide visual inspection of the device. Pay special attention to:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul style="margin-left:40px">\r\n\t<li>case (covers) their corners and joints.</li>\r\n\t<li>ports (USB, jack, micro SD card reader slot, etc).</li>\r\n\t<li>display (please refer to the <a href="http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/515%20%7C%20Mini/Visual%20display%20defects%20classification">visual display defects classification</a>&nbsp;page, in order to provide better diagnostic).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If device doesn&rsquo;t power on (or doesn&rsquo;t load into the main menu):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Remove the back cover and provide visual inspecton of the the PCBA (pay attention to the traces of leakege, burn,&nbsp;corrsion, dirt, etc).</li>\r\n\t<li>Check all wires and cables connections. Re-connect if needed.</li>\r\n\t<li>Measure the battery voltage - battery charge level value should be more or equal to 3.9V&nbsp;(charge or replace battery if needed). Please provide charging for at lest 8h and with known operational external charger and USB cable.</li>\r\n\t<li>Try to power on.</li>\r\n\t<li>If no result, please replace internal memory microSD card with with SDSN (SD card serial number) detection microSD card.</li>\r\n\t<li>Try to power on.</li>\r\n\t<li>If no result, please provide&nbsp;<a href="http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/515%20%7C%20Mini/Internal%20micro%20SD%20card%20replacement">Unit Replacement Program procedure</a>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If device powers on:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Update FW to the <a href="https://www.pocketbook-int.com/support/pocketbook-mini">latest </a>version and check customers claim.</li>\r\n\t<li>If problem still persist, please provide <a href="http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/515%20%7C%20Mini/Internal%20micro%20SD%20card%20replacement">internal&nbsp;microSD card replacement</a>.</li>\r\n\t<li>If no solution without PCBA or display replacement is available, please provide&nbsp;<a href="http://service.pocketbook-int.com/devices/515%20%7C%20Mini/Internal%20micro%20SD%20card%20replacement">Unit Replacement Program procedure</a>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Additionally (post repair actions):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Provide additional visual inspection of the display (pay special attention to the lines, dots, spots and front light quality).</li>\r\n\t<li>Check Wi-Fi connection.</li>\r\n\t<li>Check microSD card slot.</li>\r\n\t<li>Check PC connection.</li>\r\n\t<li>Check charging process.</li>\r\n\t<li>Update FW to the latest version.</li>\r\n\t<li>Clean device, if needed.</li>\r\n</ol>	2017-12-12 12:29:01.089782+00	2017-12-12 19:51:45.443564+00	3
